HEADWORD: Catallacta
<hw>Cat`al*lac"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/. See <er>Catallactics</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
division of Protozoa, of which <gen>Magosph⟦ae⟧ra</gen> is the type.
They exist both in a myxopod state, with branched pseudopodia, and in
the form of ciliated bodies united in free, spherical
colonies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

